===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}{{wp|zh:,yue:,lzh:,gan:,nan:Sòng (Chiu),en:Song dynasty,Song (Chinese surname),Song (state)}}

===Etymology===
Unclear. Possibly related to {{och-l|崧|tr=*suŋ}}, {{och-l|宗|tr=*tsˤuŋh}}, {{och-l|崇|tr=*dzruŋ}}, {{och-l|聳|tr=*soŋʔ}} or {{och-l|竦|tr=*soŋʔ}}. It is occasionally written for {{och-l|宗|tr=*tsˤuŋh}} in the Tsinghua Bamboo Slips 繫年, and is suspected to be a phonetic loan for {{och-l|竦|tr=*soŋʔ}} in the Shuihudi Qin Bamboo Texts 日書甲·詰.

